 are supermassive in the case of ultralight axions. For the QCD\naxion, the typical BH mass formed from axion star collapse is $M_{\\rm BH}\\sim\n3.4 (f_a/0.6 M_{pl})^{1.2} M_\\odot$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 15 Sep 2016 16:30:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 18 Oct 2016 16:04:41 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 9 Mar 2017 15:51:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-04-05"}
