 reaches a maximum value\na short time later before smoothing outward. Using momentum thickness as a\nlength scale and the streamwise velocity fluctuations at the location of this\nouter peak as a velocity scale, free surface bursting and air entrainment onset\nare found to depend in some way on Weber number and agreement is found with\nscaling arguments for air entrainment presented by Brocchini and Pregrine (J.\nFluid Mech., 499, 225-254, 2001).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 16 Sep 2016 15:21:39 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 28 Mar 2017 16:45:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-03-29"}
